text: Annobón is a province of Equatorial Guinea. It is the island of Annobón and its associated islets in the Gulf of Guinea. The capital city is San Antonio de Palé. The other town on the island is Mabana. The island's main industries are fishing and forestry. Annobón is an extinct volcano. The main island measures about long by wide. Its highest peak is Quioveo, which rises .
